Election 2019

Election / Elección

Notice is hereby given that the City of Bunker Hill Village will be holding

A General Election  on Saturday, May 4, 2019.

 Please click here for candidate letter with important election information.

Please click here for the latest list of candidates that have filed for election.

 Voting Information

Voting will be held at City Hall, 11977 Memorial Drive

Early Voting will be available on weekdays:

Monday, April 22 to Tuesday, April 30. 

Voting hours are 7:30 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. 

 Extended hours for early voting are available: 

Thursday, April 25 and Tuesday April 30 

7:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m.

Voting on Election Day, Saturday, May 4:  

7:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m.

Contact City Secretary, Britique Williams if you need a "mail in" ballot

The last day to request an application in person for a “mail in ballet” is Friday, April 19, 2019.  City Hall will be open from 9:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. for this purpose only.

* * * * * * * * * * * 

The "Candidate Forum"  has been rescheduled for Tuesday, April 23, 2019 at 6:00 p.m.
